Use Case: Patient Experience
Patient-centricity is achieved when a health system places the consumer at the
center of the health care model and adopts achieving the goals and objectives of
the consumer as their primary mission. It addresses six customer needs:
1. You know me
2. You know who I am
3. You know my preferences
4. You know how to improve my health
5. You know how to guide me
6. I know you value me
The patient-centricity embraces the perspective of the patient by cutting through
each of the functional silos of a health system.
The approach empowers patients to become active participants in the achievement
of their health goals. It also empowers care givers to adopt a consumer-centric
perspective by providing them with a a 360
0
longitudinal perspective of the patient.

14
Patient Relationship Management system
helps personalize the care to patients across
Partners
Customer Relationship - Develop enterprise patient relationships to make and present a single view of
the patient during all customer facing interactions.
360 View of Customer - Integrate real time analysis of past, present and future data into each patient
interaction. Recognize patient history in problem resolution and demonstrate we are insightful about the
patient.
Customer Needs and Preference - Document and abide by communications, treatment and wellness
preferences. Meet the patient at their place of preference demonstrate we anticipate your needs.
Personalized Health - Listen and adapt to the patient-members personalized objectives for their health.
Enable them through wellness, clinical and care excellence across the patients desired communications
modalities
Customer Navigation - Provide patient with seamless navigation across clinical and non-clinical touch-
points. Develop clear metric/ scorecard for patient experience, and embed processes for ongoing patient
insights/ feedback.
